-- Australia Starts A$1 Billion Fund to Cut Manufacturing Pollution
-- B y   J a s o n   S c o t t
-- 2012-02-15T23:45:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/australia-starts-a-1-billion-fund-to-cut-manufacturing-pollution.html
Australia  launched a A$1 billion
fund designed to aid manufacturers improve  energy efficiency  and
reduce pollution. The Clean Technology Investment Programs will
provide grants to help manufacturers buy new plant and equipment
which cuts energy costs or reduces carbon pollution, Industry
and Innovation Minister  Greg Combet  said in an emailed statement
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
